Global Intrauterine Contraceptive Device Market Insights
Intrauterine Contraceptive Device Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Intrauterine Contraceptive Device Market Overview
The global Intrauterine Contraceptive Device (IUCD) market was valued at approximately USD 3.5 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 4.6% from 2024 to 2030. The increasing adoption of long-acting reversible contraception methods, along with rising awareness regarding family planning, is expected to drive the market growth. IUCDs are becoming more popular due to their effectiveness, affordability, and ease of use. As healthcare systems worldwide focus on offering accessible reproductive health solutions, the demand for intrauterine devices is anticipated to rise significantly.

